Starting the New Year right with one less stress in the kitchen, a happy husband, and a delicious dinner with @shanfoodsglobal * Full Recipe Below * 

The way to my Pakistani American husband’s heart is through his stomach 😂 @shanfoodsglobal mixed spices are the perfect way to celebrate gratitude and bond with your family, guests, and friends. For someone like myself who isn’t well versed in the kitchen these mixed spice recipes are a breeze to follow, literally fool proof! 

I finished cooking two meals in 35 mins and let me just say I am beyond proud of myself! Thank you @shanfoodsglobal for an amazing start to the new year!

So here’s how i did it! 
Prep time: 5 mins 
Cook time: 30-35 mins Air fryer and stove top 

🛒✨SHOPPING LIST ✨🛒
onions
tomatoes 
cilantro
garlic & ginger paste 
lemons or lemon juice
green chilies 
whole chicken ( one that will fit in your air fryer 3-4 lbs )
ground beef 2.2 lbs
Shan’s mixes Keema + Lahori Charga 

🤍 Lahori Charga Recipe: 
Step 1. Season small whole 3-4lb Chicken with following:
1-2 tablespoons - GARLIC GINGER PASTE
8 tablespoons - LEMON JUICE
1-2 cups - COOKING OIL
1 or half the Shan LAHORI CHARGA MIXED SPICE PACKET

Step 2. Cook Marinated Chicken in Air Fryer at 400 for 30-35 mins *breast side down*

• while the chicken is in the air fryer start your keema •

🤍 Keema Recipe:

Step 1. Heat 1 cup of cooking oil, fry 3 medium onions finely chopped until transparent

1-2 tablespoons garlic paste tablespoons ginger paste, Shan Keema Mix (1 packet dissolved in ½ cup of water) and 2.2 of grounded/minced meat of choice. 

Step 2. Add 2 medium diced tomatoes and 1-2 cups of water. Cover and cook over low heat (20-30 minutes) until the meat is tender tender. I added aloo (potatoes) 

Step 3. Add 3-4 medium, chopped green chiles finely, 2 tbsp. coriander / chopped fresh coriander and cook until what the oil separates from the meat. Drain excess oil, is desired. 

35 mins later you have 2 meals to serve with sides of your choice! I served my dishes with a Greek inspired styled salad 🥗

What is Cool Sculpting?

CoolSculpting works by delivering precisly targeted low temperatures to fat cells beneath the skin. The fat cells freeze, become crystallized and die. The precisely controlled method of cooling is called Cryolipolysis® and was developed by scientists and physicians at Harvard.

Here’s how I made the most out of my cool sculpting experience:

Massages:
A minute massage also helps accelerate the elimination process of fat cells. All of the dead fat cells are permanently eliminated from the body through lymphatic drainage.

Water: 
Drinking plenty of water supports your body’s natural processes for waste removal. Dehydration causes the body to retain fluids, which can lead to swelling.

The GYM:

FOOD:
Being mindful of the food you eat can promote better digestion, keep you full with less food, and influence wiser choices about what you eat in the future. It also helps curb emotional eating and helps you connect with your body’s needs.

For those who are unfamiliar with this community, I come from a background of mixed Greek and Italian heritage, and I am a second-generation American Muslim Revert. ☪️🇬🇷🇵🇰🇮🇹 

Prior to meeting my husband, I embraced a carefree and artistic lifestyle, often being seen as the "eccentric" art enthusiast with vibrant hair and paint-stained clothes. 
My free spirit called to embrace Islam, and it was through Allah's guidance that I found my path. 

In 2010, I had the pleasure of meeting my beloved partner, Subhan. Right from our very first date, Subhan knew that I was the one for him, and he promised to marry me. Exactly five years later, we celebrated our union with a grand wedding that blended both Greek, Italian and Pakistani traditions.  Our honeymoon took us on an impromptu journey to Mecca. I remember feeling a mix of nervousness and fear, but that trip ended up transitioning my life in ways I could never have imagined. Although I may not have been able to pray or recite in the "proper" manner, I can genuinely say that I poured my heart and soul into Salah, shedding tears of purity, pain and joy

I prayed for clarity and the strength to make wise decisions during challenging times.  That same year, I was gifted with the arrival of Saleem, followed by the unexpected joy of baby Ava. In the blink of an eye, my life underwent a profound transformation. The meaning of life was redefined for me, and I felt a deep sense of urgency to spread goodness and radiate light, serving as a role model for peace and unity. As a mother, my greatest desire is for my children to thrive in a world filled with peace and happiness. When I look at your child, I see my own, and I advocate for equal opportunities and fairness for all.  We are all interconnected, with the spirits of those who came before us living on within us at a cellular level. I share in the pain felt by our children, and it is both heartwarming and bittersweet to witness their ability to liberate so many of us.  Where there’s resistance and doubt, Allah calls us closer. 🤲🏼🤍
